insert into Reviews
	values('ur85351024','This review contains spoilers.Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels is a British comedy movie that premiered in 1998. The movie is directed and written by Guy Ritchie. The movie stars Nick Moran, Jason Flemyng, Dexter Fletcher, and Jason Statham. A group of friends put together a large sum of money to enter into a high-stakes game. They unfortunately lose and find themselves indebted to a ruthless gangster that employs a debt collector.Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels is a solid comedy movie. This movie highlights the ridiculous plot turns that the story goes through. The story is able to keep this all together by having the four characters that the audience knows be extremely likable. Even through all the trials and failures that the characters embark on they have supremely likable qualities that the audience will laugh at and side with them on.The direction is elementary. This is owed to Guy Ritchie being an amateur, however the direction is entertaining enough. I enjoyed the story and there were not problems in understanding the directors intent. The direction is bland. However the writing in this movie is incredibly sharp and interesting. All of the characters feel distinct.I would recommend Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels.Grade: B',9,'27 February 2021','0120735');
