insert into Reviews
	values('ur57910549','Despite DEAD POETS SOCIETY is on IMDBs top 250 and it has even achieved a cult status I hadnt seen it until a few months ago. And after watching it, not only I loved it, but I could also why its still loved by many to this day.The movie is set on a boarding school in 1959. After a meeting of the dean with the teachers, is picked as the new litterature professor John Keating (Robin Williams in one of his greatest performances). Keatings way of teaching is very revolutionary because he teaches students the art of the Carpe Diem. And soon his students restart Keatings secret group called Dead Poets Society discussing poems and their dreams.Since there are already lots of reviews for this movie and almost everything about this movie has been said, I wont say anything more. Suffice to say that, thanks to great performances by everyone (not only Robin Williams, but also by Ethan Hawke in his debut, former Hitchcock movies supporting player Norman Lloyd and Robert Sean Leonard as a fellow student), nice cinematography, good soundtrack and a great message (the one of making your life extraordinary) this is truly a classic that has to be seen at least once. It truly deserves all the praise',9,'12 October 2019','0097165');
