insert into Reviews
	values('ur3522562','10/10... arguably the best ever Indian movie. I dont like to repeat on the statements which my fellow reviewers have already expressed. What more you can say of this movie..a masterpiece, oh no!! I think you have to term a word which is more superlative than "superlative". Its a pity the year "Pather Panchali" was released there was no Oscar category for foreign language films, otherwise, India would have won one, of course, if the Indian government had chose to send this above the bollywood movies.I liked one of the comments of the reviewers, if Hollywood is dumb then bollywood is dumber. Really speaking, I doubt if anyone in India can ever cross the brilliance of this film, hailed as a masterpiece! At least tell me any Bwood films which even comes half close, not even the over rated "Lagaan"!! This movie and of course, other Rays movies are intelligent, real and visualistic art. So what are the bwood ones: tissue papers....and the worst part of it is years after years these "dumber" movies have been sent for Oscar nominations incessantly! Time to grow up bwood, isnt it?? And what the foreigners see?? The scraps of the traditional bollywood "dumber" movies; what they miss: the excellence of the regional Indian movies!! Hey, are you listening Bollywood??',10,'10 July 2004','0048473');
